Xbox Lounges Open Nationwide<br>
<br>
On Saturday, November 23, Xbox Lounges opened in 11 Vans skateparks across the country, from California to Washington, D.C. Nine of the lounges are equipped with Xbox Live online gameplay. Special guest appearances by local radio DJs helped kick off the festivities, as DJs gave away hundreds of cool prizes like Xbox T-shirts, hats, skatepark passes, and of course Xbox games, including MechAssault, Tony Hawk Pro Skater 4, Tom Clancy's Splinter Cell, and Blinx.<br>
<br>
The parks were packed all day, and it was standing room only in the Xbox Lounges. Skaters took a breather from ollies, grinds, and airwalks to mosey over to the Xbox Lounges, which are set up with four Xbox consoles (one with Xbox Live), killer games, sofas—the works. All comers had a blast playing MechAssault online, as well as the offline titles.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.xbox.com/NR/rdonlyres/CADA80E1-34C9-44F7-88BE-15F4A6682839/0/ilmlivevansopening0004.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
